Print methods

Source: R/AllGenerics.R, R/print-methods.R
print.Rd

Provides print methods for the objects from the package melt.

Usage

# S4 method for EL
print(x, digits = max(3L, getOption("digits") - 3L), ...)

# S4 method for SummaryLM
print(
  x,
  digits = max(3L, getOption("digits") - 3L),
  signif.stars = getOption("show.signif.stars"),
  ...
)

# S4 method for logLikEL
print(x, digits = getOption("digits"), ...)

# S4 method for ELT
print(x, digits = getOption("digits"), ...)

Arguments

x

An object to be printed.

...

Further arguments passed to other methods.

digits

The number of significant digits to be passed to format().

signif.stars

A single logical. If TRUE, ‘significance stars’ are printed for each coefficient.

Examples

# model
fit <- el_lm(mpg ~ wt, data = mtcars)

# output
fit
#> 
#> Empirical Likelihood: lm 
#> 
#> Maximum EL estimates:
#> (Intercept)          wt 
#>      37.285      -5.344 
#> 
#> Chisq: 439.1, df: 1, Pr(>Chisq): < 2.2e-16
#> 
#> EL evaluation: not converged 
#> 

# empirical log-likelihood
logLik(fit)
#> 'Empirical log Lik.' -110.9035 (df=2)

# output summary
summary(fit)
#> 
#> Call:
#> el_lm(formula = mpg ~ wt, data = mtcars)
#> 
#> Coefficients:
#>             Estimate Chisq Pr(>Chisq)    
#> (Intercept)   37.285 443.3     <2e-16 ***
#> wt            -5.344 439.1     <2e-16 ***
#> ---
#> Signif. codes:  0 ‘***’ 0.001 ‘**’ 0.01 ‘*’ 0.05 ‘.’ 0.1 ‘ ’ 1
#> 
#> Chisq: 439.1, df: 1, Pr(>Chisq): < 2.2e-16 
#> 
#> Constrained EL: not converged 
#> 

# equivalent results by testing each parameter separately
elt(fit, lhs = c(1, 0))
#> 
#> Empirical Likelihood Test
#> 
#> Significance level: 0.05, Calibration: Chi-square 
#> 
#> Statistic: 443.2858, Critical value: 3.841459 
#> 
#> p-value: < 2.2204e-16 
#> 
elt(fit, lhs = c(0, 1))
#> 
#> Empirical Likelihood Test
#> 
#> Significance level: 0.05, Calibration: Chi-square 
#> 
#> Statistic: 439.0823, Critical value: 3.841459 
#> 
#> p-value: < 2.2204e-16 
#>
